<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Help - Graduation Ticket Scanner</title>
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #ffffff, #66ccff);
        color: #333;
        text-align: center;
        padding: 20px;
      }
      .container {
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: auto;
        background: white;
        padding: 20px;
        border-radius: 10px;
        box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
      }
      h1 {
        color: #222;
      }
      h2 {
        color: #0073e6;
      }
      p {
        text-align: left;
      }
      .important {
        font-weight: bold;
        color: #d9534f;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Help Guide: Graduation Ticket Scanner</h1>

      <h2>Scanning Tickets</h2>
      <p>
        Click on the <strong>"Waiting for scan..."</strong> terminal to activate
        the scanner.
      </p>
      <p>
        The scanner
        <span class="important">must be outlined in blue</span> before you can
        scan a ticket. If it's not outlined in blue, click the terminal to
        activate it.
      </p>

      <h2>Importing Data (Admin Only)</h2>
      <p>The <strong>Import</strong> button is password-protected.</p>
      <p>
        Only administrators with the correct password can import new student and
        ticket data.
      </p>

      <h2>Exporting Data (Admin Only)</h2>
      <p>The <strong>Export</strong> button is also password-protected.</p>
      <p>
        This function exports all student names and their corresponding ticket
        codes to a spreadsheet.
      </p>

      <h2>Reverting the Last Import (Admin Only)</h2>
      <p>
        The <strong>Revert Last Import</strong> button acts as an
        <span class="important">undo function</span> for the most recent import
        and is also password protected.
      </p>
      <p>Use this feature if an import was done incorrectly.</p>

      <h2>Handling Invalid Tickets</h2>
      <p>
        If a ticket is invalid, an <strong>Override</strong> button will appear.
      </p>
      <p>
        The override function allows you to bypass ticket validation, but
        <span class="important">you must sign off</span> for authorization.
      </p>
      <h2>Admin Test Tickets</h2>
      <p>Use the following test tickets to verify scanner functionality:</p>
